  ```
- **Coverage Delta**: These tests would exercise:
  - onElection scheduling of load operations
  - onResignation scheduling of unload operations
  - isActive state checking for both operations
  - TopicPartition computation for __consumer_offsets
  - Leader epoch handling
  - Integration with coordinator runtime loader

### Failure Mode 4: Missing Test Coverage for Metadata Updates and Topic Deletion Handling
- **Risk**: MEDIUM
- **Code Location**: GroupCoordinatorService.java ~line 2236-2310 (onMetadataUpdate and handleTopicsDeletion methods)
- **Description**: The `onMetadataUpdate()` method handles cluster metadata changes and calls `handleTopicsDeletion()` to clean up offsets for deleted topics. This is complex logic with NO dedicated test coverage. The untested scenarios include: (1) Propagating metadata updates to runtime, (2) Extracting deleted topic IDs from delta, (3) Scheduling write-all operations for multiple deleted topics, (4) Error handling when offset/state cleanup fails, (5) Concurrent metadata updates during offset operations. Topic deletion is a critical operation that must clean up all committed offsets.
- **Proposed Test**:
  ```java
  @Test
  public void testOnMetadataUpdateWithDeletedTopics() throws Exception {
      CoordinatorRuntime<GroupCoordinatorShard, CoordinatorRecord> runtime = mockRuntime();
      GroupCoordinatorService service = new GroupCoordinatorServiceBuilder()
          .setConfig(createConfig())
          .setRuntime(runtime)
          .build(true);

      // Create metadata delta with deleted topics
      MetadataDelta delta = mock(MetadataDelta.class);
      MetadataImage newImage = mock(MetadataImage.class);

      TopicsDelta topicsDelta = mock(TopicsDelta.class);
      Set<Uuid> deletedTopicIds = Set.of(Uuid.randomUuid(), Uuid.randomUuid());
      when(topicsDelta.deletedTopicIds()).thenReturn(deletedTopicIds);
      when(topicsDelta.image()).thenReturn(mock(MetadataImage.TopicsImage.class));
      when(delta.topicsDelta()).thenReturn(topicsDelta);

      when(runtime.scheduleWriteAllOperation(
          ArgumentMatchers.eq("on-topics-deleted"),
          ArgumentMatchers.any()
      )).thenReturn(List.of(
          CompletableFuture.completedFuture(null),
          CompletableFuture.completedFuture(null)
      ));

      when(runtime.scheduleWriteAllOperation(
          ArgumentMatchers.eq("maybe-cleanup-share-group-state"),
          ArgumentMatchers.any()
      )).thenReturn(List.of(
          CompletableFuture.completedFuture(null)
      ));

      service.onMetadataUpdate(delta, newImage);

      verify(runtime, times(1)).onMetadataUpdate(ArgumentMatchers.any(), ArgumentMatchers.any());
      verify(runtime, times(1)).scheduleWriteAllOperation(
          ArgumentMatchers.eq("on-topics-deleted"),
          ArgumentMatchers.any()
      );
      verify(runtime, times(1)).scheduleWriteAllOperation(
          ArgumentMatchers.eq("maybe-cleanup-share-group-state"),
          ArgumentMatchers.any()
      );
  }

  @Test
  public void testOnMetadataUpdateHandlesDeletedTopicCleanupErrors() throws Exception {
      CoordinatorRuntime<GroupCoordinatorShard, CoordinatorRecord> runtime = mockRuntime();
      GroupCoordinatorService service = new GroupCoordinatorServiceBuilder()
          .setConfig(createConfig())
          .setRuntime(runtime)
          .build(true);

      MetadataDelta delta = mock(MetadataDelta.class);
      MetadataImage newImage = mock(MetadataImage.class);

      TopicsDelta topicsDelta = mock(TopicsDelta.class);
      when(topicsDelta.deletedTopicIds()).thenReturn(Set.of(Uuid.randomUuid()));
      when(topicsDelta.image()).thenReturn(mock(MetadataImage.TopicsImage.class));
      when(delta.topicsDelta()).thenReturn(topicsDelta);

      CompletableFuture<Void> failedFuture = new CompletableFuture<>();
      failedFuture.completeExceptionally(new RuntimeException("Write failed"));

      when(runtime.scheduleWriteAllOperation(
          ArgumentMatchers.eq("on-topics-deleted"),
          ArgumentMatchers.any()
      )).thenReturn(List.of(failedFuture));

      when(runtime.scheduleWriteAllOperation(
          ArgumentMatchers.eq("maybe-cleanup-share-group-state"),
          ArgumentMatchers.any()
      )).thenReturn(List.of(CompletableFuture.completedFuture(null)));

      // The method should log errors but not throw
      assertDoesNotThrow(() -> service.onMetadataUpdate(delta, newImage));
  }
  ```
- **Coverage Delta**: These tests would exercise:
  - Metadata update delegation to runtime
  - TopicsDelta extraction and processing
  - Deleted topic identification and collection
  - Write-all operation scheduling for offset cleanup
  - Write-all operation scheduling for share group state cleanup
  - Error logging and handling for cleanup failures
  - Metadata image wrapping (KRaftCoordinatorMetadataImage)
  - State consistency after metadata updates

### Failure Mode 5: Missing Test Coverage for Transaction Completion with Error Scenarios
- **Risk**: MEDIUM
- **Code Location**: GroupCoordinatorService.java ~line 2173-2200 (completeTransaction method)
- **Description**: The `completeTransaction()` method finalizes producer transactions by writing transaction markers. This operation has NO visible test coverage. Untested scenarios include: (1) Completion with COMMIT result, (2) Completion with ABORT result, (3) Error handling when transactional write fails, (4) Validation of topic partition (must be __consumer_offsets), (5) State of transaction coordinator when completion fails. Transaction completeness is critical for exactly-once semantics.
- **Proposed Test**:
  ```java
  @Test
  public void testCompleteTransactionWithCommitResult() throws ExecutionException, InterruptedException, TimeoutException {
      CoordinatorRuntime<GroupCoordinatorShard, CoordinatorRecord> runtime = mockRuntime();
      GroupCoordinatorService service = new GroupCoordinatorServiceBuilder()
          .setConfig(createConfig())
          .setRuntime(runtime)
          .build(true);

      TopicPartition tp = new TopicPartition(Topic.GROUP_METADATA_TOPIC_NAME, 0);

      when(runtime.scheduleTransactionCompletion(
          ArgumentMatchers.eq("write-txn-marker"),
          ArgumentMatchers.eq(tp),
          ArgumentMatchers.eq(100L),
          ArgumentMatchers.eq((short) 5),
          ArgumentMatchers.eq(1),
          ArgumentMatchers.eq(TransactionResult.COMMIT),
          ArgumentMatchers.eq((short) 1)
      )).thenReturn(CompletableFuture.completedFuture(null));

      CompletableFuture<Void> future = service.completeTransaction(
          tp,
          100L,
          (short) 5,
          1,
          TransactionResult.COMMIT,
          (short) 1
      );

      assertDoesNotThrow(() -> future.get(5, TimeUnit.SECONDS));
  }

  @Test
  public void testCompleteTransactionWithAbortResult() throws ExecutionException, InterruptedException, TimeoutException {
      CoordinatorRuntime<GroupCoordinatorShard, CoordinatorRecord> runtime = mockRuntime();
      GroupCoordinatorService service = new GroupCoordinatorServiceBuilder()
          .setConfig(createConfig())
          .setRuntime(runtime)
          .build(true);

      TopicPartition tp = new TopicPartition(Topic.GROUP_METADATA_TOPIC_NAME, 0);

      when(runtime.scheduleTransactionCompletion(
          ArgumentMatchers.any(),
          ArgumentMatchers.eq(tp),
          ArgumentMatchers.any(),
          ArgumentMatchers.any(),
          ArgumentMatchers.any(),
          ArgumentMatchers.eq(TransactionResult.ABORT),
          ArgumentMatchers.any()
      )).thenReturn(CompletableFuture.completedFuture(null));

      CompletableFuture<Void> future = service.completeTransaction(
          tp,
          100L,
          (short) 5,
          1,
          TransactionResult.ABORT,
          (short) 1
      );

      assertDoesNotThrow(() -> future.get(5, TimeUnit.SECONDS));
  }

  @Test
  public void testCompleteTransactionWithInvalidTopicPartition() throws Exception {
      CoordinatorRuntime<GroupCoordinatorShard, CoordinatorRecord> runtime = mockRuntime();
      GroupCoordinatorService service = new GroupCoordinatorServiceBuilder()
          .setConfig(createConfig())
          .setRuntime(runtime)
          .build(true);

      TopicPartition invalidTp = new TopicPartition("other-topic", 0);

      CompletableFuture<Void> future = service.completeTransaction(
          invalidTp,
          100L,
          (short) 5,
          1,
          TransactionResult.COMMIT,
          (short) 1
      );

      assertTrue(future.isCompletedExceptionally());
      assertThrows(ExecutionException.class, future::get);
  }

  @Test
  public void testCompleteTransactionWhenNotActive() throws Exception {
      CoordinatorRuntime<GroupCoordinatorShard, CoordinatorRecord> runtime = mockRuntime();
      GroupCoordinatorService service = new GroupCoordinatorServiceBuilder()
          .setConfig(createConfig())
          .setRuntime(runtime)
          .build();

      TopicPartition tp = new TopicPartition(Topic.GROUP_METADATA_TOPIC_NAME, 0);

      CompletableFuture<Void> future = service.completeTransaction(
          tp,
          100L,
          (short) 5,
          1,
          TransactionResult.COMMIT,
          (short) 1
      );

      assertTrue(future.isCompletedExceptionally());
      assertFutureThrows(Errors.COORDINATOR_NOT_AVAILABLE.exception().getClass(), future);
  }
  ```
- **Coverage Delta**: These tests would exercise:
  - Transaction completion with COMMIT result
  - Transaction completion with ABORT result
  - Producer ID and epoch handling
  - Coordinator epoch tracking
  - Transaction version handling
  - Topic partition validation (must be __consumer_offsets)
  - Exception throwing for invalid topic partitions
  - isActive state checking
  - Runtime scheduler integration for transaction completion
  - Error propagation for not-active coordinator

## File References

- **Main Implementation**: `group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorService.java` (lines 160-2433)
  - `commitOffsets()` method: lines 2062-2093
  - `deleteOffsets()` method: lines 2139-2167
  - `onElection()` method: lines 2206-2215
  - `onResignation()` method: lines 2221-2230
  - `onMetadataUpdate()` method: lines 2236-2254
  - `handleTopicsDeletion()` method: lines 2262-2310
  - `completeTransaction()` method: lines 2173-2200

- **Existing Tests**: `group-coordinator/src/test/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorServiceTest.java`
  - Current test coverage: ~100+ tests for consumer group heartbeats, streams group heartbeats, share group operations, describe groups, list groups, fetch offsets, and transactional offset commits
  - Missing coverage: No tests for regular offset commits, offset deletions, partition leadership changes, or transaction completion

